bin_dir.description: The full bin path of the modules executables

create_cmd_bin.description: The full bin path & command used on create

destroy_cmd_bin.description: The full bin path & command used on destroy

downloaded.description: Whether gcloud was downloaded or not

wait.description: An output to use when you want to depend on cmd finishing

additional_components.description: Additional gcloud CLI components to install. Defaults to none. Valid value are components listed in `gcloud components list`

create_cmd_body.description: On create, the command body you'd like to run with your entrypoint.

create_cmd_entrypoint.description: On create, the command entrypoint you'd like to use. Can also be set to a custom script. Module's bin directory will be prepended to path.

create_cmd_triggers.description: List of any additional triggers for the create command execution.

destroy_cmd_body.description: On destroy, the command body you'd like to run with your entrypoint.

destroy_cmd_entrypoint.description: On destroy, the command entrypoint you'd like to use.  Can also be set to a custom script. Module's bin directory will be prepended to path.

enabled.description: Flag to optionally disable usage of this module.

gcloud_sdk_version.description: The gcloud sdk version to download.

module_depends_on.description: List of modules or resources this module depends on.

platform.description: Platform CLI will run on. Defaults to linux. Valid values: linux, darwin

service_account_key_file.description: Path to service account key file to run `gcloud auth activate-service-account` with. Optional.

skip_download.description: Whether to skip downloading gcloud (assumes gcloud is already available outside the module)

upgrade.description: Whether to upgrade gcloud at runtime

use_tf_google_credentials_env_var.description: Use GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS environment variable to run `gcloud auth activate-service-account` with. Optional.

controller_image.description:
Docker image uri for the controller service
    (fully qualified uri, meaning with tag)"

custom_domain.description:
(Optional) Custom Domain for the UI (e.g. crmint.example.com).
    Leave this value empty to skip.

database_availability_type.description: Database availability type. Defaults to one zone.

database_instance_name.description: Name for the Cloud SQL instance.

database_name.description: Name of the database in your Cloud SQL instance.

database_project_id.description: Database GCP project to use. Defaults to `var.project_id`.

database_region.description: Database region to setup a Cloud SQL instance. Defaults to `var.region`

database_tier.description: Database instance machine tier. Defaults to a small instance.

iap_support_email.description: Support email used for configuring IAP

network_project_id.description: Network GCP project to use. Defaults to `var.project_id`.

use_vpc.description: Configures the database with a private IP. Default to true.
